('d8cdf5b8-5fae-5b8f-b244-f68b51ec4549', '02713a3e-ded7-4f5d-8e3c-ff77f8e796b6', 60, 'Senior RPLS MARK LEE SHERLEY (license #5326, granted 1999); est. age ~57 (license_tenure_proxy assuming typical RPLS-earn age of 30 — TX RPLS requires 4yr college + 4yr supervised survey-in-training + state exam); firm tenure 27yr. Solo RPLS = single principal, classic owner-of-record.', 65, '27yr-tenured firm with 1 active RPLS — TX RPLS license is a 4yr-college + 4yr-apprentice + exam-gated skilled-trade moat; firm passes the >5yr in-business hard gate; vertical has documented recurring B2B from oil/gas ROW + construction stake-out + ALTA + FEMA elev certs. Default L2 mid-range pending enrichment-time confirmation of staff count + recurring program mix (homebuilder logos / MSA language).', 60, 'Solo RPLS for 27+ years — owner has not added a second RPLS / has not been training a credentialed successor. Default vertical-baseline: TX surveying firms with solo RPLS rarely have online project portals, drone/UAV mention, 3D laser scanning, or GPS RTK base station references on their websites — modern tech-stack absence is a measurable coasting signal (industry-standard since 2018). (Default scoring — confirm individual coasting tells at enrichment-time live-fetch.)', 71, 'Greater Houston metro (The Woodlands, Montgomery County) — West Houston growth + Harris-Galveston Subsidence District annual monitoring + flood-zone FEMA work. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman (NASDAQ:BWMN) + Westwood (Endeavour Capital) are PE-backed rollup platforms in TX; large-AEC strategics (Stantec, WSP, AECOM, Kimley-Horn, Cobb Fendley, LJA) only bolt-on $5M+ rev firms — sub-$5M independents are structurally under-targeted. ETA/search-fund appetite emerging fast 2024-2026 (top-15 vertical in Stanford Search Fund Study). +2 baseline boost for solo/2-RPLS metros = opportunity zone.', 63, 'B_forward', 'Senior RPLS MARK LEE SHERLEY (granted 1999, est. age ~57 via license_tenure_proxy, 27yr firm tenure); FOUR POINTS in The Woodlands, Montgomery County. Solo RPLS firm. L1 60 / L2 65 / L3 60 / L4 71 → final 63, tier B_forward. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman + Westwood active in TX surveying-firm PE rollup; sub-$5M independent universe is structurally under-targeted. Forward to ETA/search-fund community.', 'AI / ops modernization play on a 27yr-tenured single-RPLS surveying firm in The Woodlands:  (1) drone/UAV survey program (~25-40% labor savings on topo + as-built); (2) 3D laser scanning + reality capture for as-built and infrastructure work; (3) online project portal for ALTA / FEMA / boundary client self-service; (4) RTK GPS base station network for sub-cm field productivity; (5) automated CAD/drafting workflow + AI plat-review. FEMA elevation cert recurring program + Harris-Galveston Subsidence District annual monitoring contracts are an underexploited annuity book here. Plausible 1.5-2× EBITDA path 18-24 months. Off-market multiple 3-5× EBITDA in current LOW-PE-attention environment; would shift to 5-7× as ETA/search-fund deal-velocity ramps 2026-2027.', 'low', 0.45),
